  <title translate="true">RmaSutra: Model Summary</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" translate="true">RmaSutra: Model Summary</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">The starting point for this model is an example SUTRA model named Rocky2D_Irregular.gpt distributed with ModelMuse but whose set up is not described in a tutorial. That model was modified by changing it from steady flow/steady transport to steady flow/transient transport. The maximum time was set to 631152000 with 100 time steps. Eight head observations have been specified. They will be converted to calibration observations. There is also an object named &quot;Flow_Factor&quot; that outlines the nodes that are part of a flow observation. To use PEST with the model we will perform the following tasks.</text></para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Make a few small but important changes to the model.</text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Activate PEST.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Define parameters to use in the model.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Define parameter groups and assign parameters to them.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Apply parameters to data sets.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If desired, define pilot points.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Apply parameters to boundary conditions.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Define observations.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Define observation groups.</text></li>
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Assign observations to observation groups.</text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="2" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Define prior information equations for Tikhonov regularization.</text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Run PEST.</text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="3" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Visualize weighted residuals.</text></li>
    </list>
    <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="·" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Visualize the modified model input.</text></li>
    </list>
  </body>
